1
00:01:37,670 --> 00:01:43,914
This area has always been difficult for ships to
navigate, so all sorts of things wash up on our shore.

2
00:01:46,175 --> 00:01:49,618
In the old days, the entire village
used to pitch in and help clean up.

3
00:01:50,078 --> 00:01:52,900
But now you lack the manpower
to accomplish such a feat.

4
00:01:54,120 --> 00:01:58,103
These waters were beautiful
once, as clear as crystal.

5
00:01:59,624 --> 00:02:00,424
Yes, I know.

6
00:02:03,786 --> 00:02:06,108
Would you be willing to
accept this as payment?

7
00:02:09,691 --> 00:02:12,293
It's a book written by the
legendary mage Flamme.

8
00:02:13,413 --> 00:02:17,416
Mistress Frieren... Is this the
only grimoire the village has?

9
00:02:17,436 --> 00:02:18,416
Yes.

10
00:02:19,637 --> 00:02:20,178
It shall do.

11
00:02:20,958 --> 00:02:23,019
We'll restore your
coast to its former glory.

12
00:02:27,802 --> 00:02:28,803
What are you doing?

13
00:02:29,283 --> 00:02:31,284
That book is a fake.

14
00:02:31,304 --> 00:02:33,186
So, you've been
studying like I told you to.

15
00:02:33,726 --> 00:02:34,586
Good girl, Fern.

16
00:02:35,678 --> 00:02:37,860
Texts attributed to
Flamme aren't real.

17
00:02:38,680 --> 00:02:40,501
This is yet another
poor imitation.

18
00:02:41,362 --> 00:02:42,923
Then why did you accept the job?

19
00:02:44,184 --> 00:02:46,306
Because that man
clearly needed our help.

20
00:02:47,386 --> 00:02:49,027
That must not be
your only reason.

21
00:02:51,209 --> 00:02:51,609
You're right.

22
00:02:52,930 --> 00:02:53,931
I'm doing this for me.

23
00:02:57,173 --> 00:02:59,435
Sounds like we have
another long stay ahead of us.

24
00:03:15,310 --> 00:03:17,351
Always a joy to see
my best customer.

25
00:03:17,992 --> 00:03:19,853
I threw in something
extra just for you.

26
00:03:20,633 --> 00:03:21,354
Thank you, ma'am.

27
00:03:22,174 --> 00:03:24,015
A gift for three
months of loyalty.

28
00:03:24,395 --> 00:03:25,996
Have you gotten
used to our village yet?

29
00:03:26,316 --> 00:03:26,737
I have.

30
00:03:27,057 --> 00:03:29,878
The shore gets awfully
cold this time of year.

31
00:03:30,279 --> 00:03:31,720
You girls be careful.

32
00:03:36,562 --> 00:03:37,863
It's winter already?

33
00:03:43,426 --> 00:03:44,507
She's still asleep.

34
00:03:46,132 --> 00:03:47,493
And this place is a mess.

35
00:03:48,434 --> 00:03:50,216
I tidied it up only yesterday.

36
00:03:50,236 --> 00:03:53,880
It's morning time.

37
00:03:54,020 --> 00:03:55,041
You need to wake up.

38
00:03:55,321 --> 00:03:56,322
There's work to do.

39
00:03:56,342 --> 00:04:09,395
The shore isn't
going to clean itself.

40
00:04:37,995 --> 00:04:39,156
Something occurred to me.

41
00:04:40,276 --> 00:04:41,017
What's that?

42
00:04:41,717 --> 00:04:46,200
I wonder if you might actually be a
rather irresponsible sort of person.

43
00:04:47,101 --> 00:04:51,783
I wake you up at a reasonable hour every
morning and get you dressed and feed you.

44
00:04:53,064 --> 00:04:55,826
You do know that I am
not your mother, don't you?

45
00:04:55,846 --> 00:04:58,527
I'm capable of
doing all that myself.

46
00:04:58,767 --> 00:04:59,228
No doubt.

47
00:04:59,668 --> 00:05:01,589
But you wouldn't be
on your feet till noon.

48
00:05:01,609 --> 00:05:02,570
Fair.

49
00:05:03,330 --> 00:05:04,331
I'm not worried about it.

50
00:05:04,911 --> 00:05:06,112
I've already given up hope.

51
00:05:07,112 --> 00:05:08,213
I apologize.

52
00:05:09,014 --> 00:05:11,877
How did you ever manage
traveling with the Heroes Party?

53
00:05:12,618 --> 00:05:15,060
I can't imagine they would
be willing to brush your hair.

54
00:05:15,701 --> 00:05:17,382
I overslept all the
time back then.

55
00:05:18,463 --> 00:05:20,165
And you never
got in trouble for it?

56
00:05:21,086 --> 00:05:23,588
I did actually,
but just the once.

57
00:05:24,429 --> 00:05:25,110
Only once?

58
00:05:26,111 --> 00:05:28,313
They must have been
uniquely patient people.

59
00:05:29,184 --> 00:05:30,765
They were unique, certainly.

60
00:05:31,505 --> 00:05:34,186
Though Heiter did often
click his tongue in disapproval.

61
00:05:35,227 --> 00:05:36,468
Sorry.

62
00:05:36,688 --> 00:05:37,328
Watch it.

63
00:05:37,408 --> 00:05:39,109
I understand, friend,
but calm down.

64
00:05:39,129 --> 00:05:42,250
Oh my, he gave you
the tongue click of rage.

65
00:05:55,617 --> 00:05:57,358
How's the big
cleanup coming along?

66
00:05:58,880 --> 00:06:01,181
I would say that we're about
two-thirds of the way there.

67
00:06:01,861 --> 00:06:04,542
Do you think it'll be ready
by the New Year's festival?

68
00:06:05,083 --> 00:06:06,243
Barely, but yes.

69
00:06:06,843 --> 00:06:11,205
In that case, I sincerely hope you'll be
able to join us in watching the sunrise.

70
00:06:11,285 --> 00:06:13,066
This time, a sight to behold.

71
00:06:21,550 --> 00:06:26,212
So this whole cleanup operation is
related to the New Year's festival?

72
00:06:27,305 --> 00:06:30,988
In this village, it's customary to welcome
the new year by watching the sunrise.

73
00:06:32,109 --> 00:06:35,112
It's something about the way
the light reflects off the clear water.

74
00:06:35,652 --> 00:06:37,254
They say that
it's quite beautiful.

75
00:06:38,375 --> 00:06:40,497
You mean you've never
gotten to see it before?

76
00:06:41,337 --> 00:06:42,999
You think that I could
wake up that early?

77
00:06:43,019 --> 00:06:45,361
That does seem unlikely.

78
00:06:46,482 --> 00:06:47,262
Let's try to hurry.

79
00:06:47,282 --> 00:06:48,904
We don't have much time.

80
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:31,521
The water quality
is looking great.

81
00:07:32,762 --> 00:07:34,863
Our work is done with
a whole night to spare.

82
00:07:35,843 --> 00:07:37,585
It hardly looks like
the same beach.

83
00:07:39,105 --> 00:07:41,487
Thank you for all your
hard work, Miss Frieren.

84
00:07:42,247 --> 00:07:45,009
Tomorrow, you'll be joining
us for the festival, right?

85
00:07:45,569 --> 00:07:45,889
Right.

86
00:07:46,610 --> 00:07:48,051
We're excited to have you.

87
00:07:49,732 --> 00:07:50,812
Have you lost your mind?

88
00:07:50,992 --> 00:07:51,913
That's so early.

89
00:07:51,933 --> 00:07:54,554
There's no way you'll be
able to wake up in time.

90
00:07:54,854 --> 00:07:56,035
It would be impossible.

91
00:07:57,096 --> 00:07:58,557
Not if I simply don't sleep.

92
00:07:59,642 --> 00:08:01,883
You're that intent on
seeing the sunrise?

93
00:08:02,623 --> 00:08:04,463
To be honest, I
couldn't care less.

94
00:08:05,184 --> 00:08:06,824
That's the reason
I'd like to see it.

95
00:08:08,384 --> 00:08:09,805
I don't understand.

96
00:08:10,445 --> 00:08:11,165
Neither do I.

97
00:08:19,928 --> 00:08:22,188
You didn't come to the
New Year's festival with us.

98
00:08:22,668 --> 00:08:23,209
Why not?

99
00:08:23,229 --> 00:08:25,189
You broke poor Heiter's heart.

100
00:08:25,569 --> 00:08:26,449
Now he's bedridden.

101
00:08:27,090 --> 00:08:28,250
What a sensitive soul.

102
00:08:28,835 --> 00:08:31,857
The only thing he's sensitive
to are the effects of his drink.

103
00:08:32,358 --> 00:08:34,679
The rest of you got to
go, so what's the issue?

104
00:08:35,800 --> 00:08:36,961
You should have been there too.

105
00:08:37,341 --> 00:08:38,582
We wanted you to enjoy it.

106
00:08:38,602 --> 00:08:41,364
It was merely a sunrise.

107
00:08:41,424 --> 00:08:43,726
I doubt it would have
brought me any joy.

108
00:08:44,306 --> 00:08:45,107
You're wrong there.

109
00:08:45,347 --> 00:08:46,228
You would have loved it.

110
00:08:46,248 --> 00:08:47,489
Why's that?

111
00:08:48,890 --> 00:08:50,671
Because you're just
that kind of person.

112
00:08:55,114 --> 00:08:55,895
She's asleep.

113
00:08:58,077 --> 00:08:58,838
She's asleep!

114
00:08:59,198 --> 00:09:03,160
Mistress Frieren, you have to wake
up, or else you'll be late to the festival!

115
00:09:03,180 --> 00:09:07,062
Mama... Who do you think
you're calling mama, young lady?

116
00:09:07,083 --> 00:09:11,025
Why exactly am I
doing this again?

117
00:09:11,045 --> 00:09:15,347
For me, Fern.

118
00:09:15,728 --> 00:09:16,428
Thank you.

119
00:09:29,167 --> 00:09:29,507
Hmm...

120
00:09:30,467 --> 00:09:31,588
It's certainly pretty.

121
00:09:32,588 --> 00:09:35,009
But I wouldn't say it's
worth waking up early for.

122
00:09:35,929 --> 00:09:38,830
Maybe Himmel didn't know
what kind of person I was after all.

123
00:09:40,230 --> 00:09:40,630
I'm off.

124
00:09:41,270 --> 00:09:44,751
I need to go back to...
Look at it, Mistress.

125
00:09:45,712 --> 00:09:46,712
It's so beautiful.

126
00:09:48,812 --> 00:09:49,673
Oh, is it?

127
00:09:51,273 --> 00:09:52,573
It's just a sunrise.

128
00:09:55,014 --> 00:09:56,315
Don't act tough to me.

129
00:09:56,655 --> 00:09:57,815
I can tell you're happy.

130
00:09:58,593 --> 00:10:01,374
Maybe so, but only
because you're smiling.

131
00:10:10,118 --> 00:10:13,480
I wouldn't have been able to see
this sunrise if I'd been on my own.

132
00:10:15,121 --> 00:10:16,121
Absolutely not.

133
00:10:16,541 --> 00:10:19,763
If I weren't here, you'd
still be snuggled up in bed.

134
00:10:25,897 --> 00:10:26,897
Are these for your family?

135
00:10:27,658 --> 00:10:29,138
It happened a long time ago.

136
00:10:29,999 --> 00:10:33,340
Demons attacked my
village and showed no mercy.

137
00:10:36,261 --> 00:10:37,082
What are you doing?

138
00:10:38,682 --> 00:10:39,643
Praying, of course.

139
00:10:40,243 --> 00:10:42,144
We return to
nothing when we die.

140
00:10:43,204 --> 00:10:44,725
I like to think we go to heaven.

141
00:10:45,661 --> 00:10:49,843
Until several thousand years ago, people
largely accepted that nothing comes after.

142
00:10:50,524 --> 00:10:52,445
But I know the
dwarves value tradition.

143
00:10:53,445 --> 00:10:56,147
I myself am skeptical
about the idea of a heaven.

144
00:10:56,767 --> 00:11:01,329
Magic can't observe the souls of the dead,
so an afterlife cannot be outright proven.

145
00:11:02,010 --> 00:11:03,871
Though it cannot
be disproven either.

146
00:11:04,604 --> 00:11:06,645
I for one don't think
it matters either way.

147
00:11:07,526 --> 00:11:08,226
I agree.

148
00:11:08,806 --> 00:11:11,868
In the grand scheme of things, I
can't say how much it truly matters.

149
00:11:12,188 --> 00:11:13,869
Careful now, oh corrupt one.

150
00:11:14,229 --> 00:11:15,229
Not very priestly.

151
00:11:16,050 --> 00:11:16,550
You're right.

152
00:11:16,930 --> 00:11:20,992
But even if a heaven doesn't exist,
I very much believe that it should.

153
00:11:21,453 --> 00:11:22,173
Why's that?

154
00:11:23,274 --> 00:11:25,495
I feel it's more
convenient that way.

155
00:11:26,655 --> 00:11:31,418
Those that kept living despite life's
hardships deserve more than just oblivion.

156
00:11:32,914 --> 00:11:33,074
Metz

157
00:12:04,599 --> 00:12:05,240
Hello there.

158
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:06,621
I thought I'd drop by.

159
00:12:07,842 --> 00:12:10,505
You act as if it hasn't
been thirty years.

160
00:12:11,966 --> 00:12:13,568
So, not very long at all, then.

161
00:12:16,210 --> 00:12:17,251
I suppose not.

162
00:12:19,373 --> 00:12:21,996
I never thought you would
take on an apprentice.

163
00:12:24,198 --> 00:12:27,481
Eisen, I came to see if there's
anything I can help you with.

164
00:12:28,563 --> 00:12:29,904
I'm not done here yet.

165
00:12:30,564 --> 00:12:35,886
I heard you paid a visit to Heiter before he
passed away, and asked him the same thing.

166
00:12:37,027 --> 00:12:38,147
How do you know about that?

167
00:12:39,328 --> 00:12:40,929
Heiter and I rode often.

168
00:12:41,509 --> 00:12:43,410
You're much friendlier
than you appear.

169
00:12:44,350 --> 00:12:46,371
Or perhaps you're
not friendly enough.

170
00:12:47,271 --> 00:12:50,473
Well, tell me, is there
anything we could do?

171
00:12:54,715 --> 00:12:55,675
Full basin.

172
00:12:56,396 --> 00:12:57,336
This takes me back.

173
00:12:58,329 --> 00:12:59,690
So you've been here before?

174
00:13:00,150 --> 00:13:00,771
Long ago.

175
00:13:01,751 --> 00:13:03,192
Long ago, she says.

176
00:13:03,752 --> 00:13:05,153
How long must that be?

177
00:13:07,014 --> 00:13:08,675
Probably in prehistoric times.

178
00:13:08,855 --> 00:13:10,556
Not even I have lived that long.

179
00:13:14,079 --> 00:13:14,599
Explain.

180
00:13:15,159 --> 00:13:16,140
What are we looking for?

181
00:13:16,780 --> 00:13:19,582
The notes of Flamme,
the legendary mage.

182
00:13:22,304 --> 00:13:23,264
If you insist.

183
00:13:23,744 --> 00:13:26,246
But you know most of our
supposed writings are fake.

184
00:13:27,222 --> 00:13:28,042
Not this one.

185
00:13:28,062 --> 00:13:30,663
I have a lead from Heiter.

186
00:13:31,263 --> 00:13:35,464
He deduced the location from
records on Flamme, left in the Holy City.

187
00:13:35,484 --> 00:13:39,886
Her genuine notes are located
somewhere in Full Basin.

188
00:13:41,226 --> 00:13:42,266
Think back, Frieren.

189
00:13:42,826 --> 00:13:44,187
You must remember that.

190
00:13:45,727 --> 00:13:49,288
His research was in-depth,
quite driven for a corrupt priest.

191
00:13:50,849 --> 00:13:51,389
Let's begin.

192
00:13:51,989 --> 00:13:54,049
We can start by
looking for a giant tree.

193
00:13:54,830 --> 00:13:55,750
A giant tree?

194
00:13:56,618 --> 00:13:57,579
That's ridiculous.

195
00:13:58,079 --> 00:13:59,660
We're in a forest full of them.

196
00:14:00,361 --> 00:14:04,183
Well, I suppose you do
have all the time in the world.

197
00:14:04,203 --> 00:14:05,164
That I do.

198
00:14:06,305 --> 00:14:09,307
But Fern doesn't like when I
work leisurely, so I'll try to be quick.

199
00:14:13,090 --> 00:14:15,031
Let's search as
efficiently as possible.

200
00:14:15,051 --> 00:14:19,414
You've changed.

201
00:14:20,755 --> 00:14:23,417
You never cared about
other people's time before.

202
00:14:25,340 --> 00:14:26,160
That's all Fern.

203
00:14:26,680 --> 00:14:29,501
She's scary when she's mad.

204
00:14:29,521 --> 00:14:30,001
Dunno.

205
00:14:30,621 --> 00:14:31,642
I'll watch myself.

206
00:15:05,758 --> 00:15:06,719
Mistress Frieren!

207
00:15:07,800 --> 00:15:11,343
I spotted a large tree growing
over some ruins to the west of here.

208
00:15:12,344 --> 00:15:12,784
This way.

209
00:15:13,925 --> 00:15:14,465
Meet you there.

210
00:15:18,169 --> 00:15:22,232
Eisen, I understand wanting
those notes, but why now?

211
00:15:23,313 --> 00:15:25,034
Because I felt sorry for you.

212
00:15:27,556 --> 00:15:29,178
Not just you, I suppose.

213
00:15:29,718 --> 00:15:31,560
I felt sorry for Himmel, too.

214
00:15:32,964 --> 00:15:38,408
Thirty years ago, at his funeral, you said that you
wished you would have gotten to know him better.

215
00:15:39,448 --> 00:15:43,771
In my humble opinion, you
should tell that to Himmel himself.

216
00:15:45,052 --> 00:15:52,176
According to legend, Flamme's notes discuss her conversations
with the dead, and how she achieved those meetings.

217
00:15:53,437 --> 00:15:58,080
Nothing more than a fairy tale, and such
dialogue with Himmel is far from my mind.

218
00:15:58,800 --> 00:16:02,483
You know more than most that
all magic started as fairy tales.

219
00:16:03,468 --> 00:16:06,029
And don't you want to learn
more about your lost friend?

220
00:16:07,170 --> 00:16:09,111
That's why I brought
this up to Heiter.

221
00:16:10,292 --> 00:16:12,573
It was evident that
you had regrets.

222
00:16:13,913 --> 00:16:15,374
We wanted to help
you through them.

223
00:16:25,239 --> 00:16:25,860
A barrier.

224
00:16:26,620 --> 00:16:27,861
And a powerful one.

225
00:16:27,941 --> 00:16:30,022
It's protecting both
the tree and the ruins.

226
00:16:33,505 --> 00:16:39,187
It's been over a thousand years now, and here
I am dancing in the palm of my master's hand.

227
00:16:41,788 --> 00:16:44,770
How is that going to keep watch?

228
00:16:44,790 --> 00:16:45,890
Oh, don't sell it short.

229
00:16:47,451 --> 00:16:48,931
This little sapling will grow.

230
00:16:49,391 --> 00:16:52,613
In a thousand years, it'll
still be protecting this place.

231
00:16:53,273 --> 00:16:55,374
Probably so, but
you'll be dead by then.

232
00:16:57,360 --> 00:16:58,661
Well, sure, but you won't be.

233
00:16:59,562 --> 00:17:05,128
Someday down the line, you're going to make a horrid mistake,
and you'll wish you had gotten to know the people around you.

234
00:17:05,908 --> 00:17:07,590
Are you asking I
get to know you?

235
00:17:08,251 --> 00:17:08,911
How needy.

236
00:17:09,292 --> 00:17:10,473
Yeah, not quite.

237
00:17:11,454 --> 00:17:20,383
All that I'm saying is when the inevitable happens, return to this
place, and I, the legendary mage Flamme, will be here to help.

238
00:17:35,279 --> 00:17:37,981
So those are Flamme's notes?

239
00:17:38,962 --> 00:17:40,223
And we're certain they're real?

240
00:17:41,064 --> 00:17:41,524
They are.

241
00:17:42,905 --> 00:17:44,086
How can you be so sure?

242
00:17:44,806 --> 00:17:47,208
Frieren was
Flamme's best student.

243
00:17:48,769 --> 00:17:50,551
Flamme, the hero
from my textbook?

244
00:17:51,151 --> 00:17:54,133
Are you telling me that
Frieren used to be her student?

245
00:17:55,034 --> 00:17:57,616
And we're positive that
she doesn't predate history?

246
00:17:58,417 --> 00:18:00,839
Doesn't say anything about
speaking with the dead.

247
00:18:00,859 --> 00:18:03,961
It was already open
to that very page.

248
00:18:05,925 --> 00:18:09,229
So she knew a thousand years ago
that I would come back here someday.

249
00:18:10,891 --> 00:18:12,172
What an unpleasant woman.

250
00:18:14,454 --> 00:18:20,701
On the very northernmost end of the continent, I arrived
at the place the people of this world call heaven.

251
00:18:21,943 --> 00:18:26,708
I now know it as Oreale,
the land where souls rest.

252
00:18:28,622 --> 00:18:30,382
Many spirits have
gathered there.

253
00:18:31,543 --> 00:18:34,143
I spoke with friends whom
I once fought alongside.

254
00:18:34,923 --> 00:18:40,544
It was the discovery of a lifetime, and will
hopefully propel the research on souls forward.

255
00:18:42,905 --> 00:18:44,465
Do you think any
of that is true?

256
00:18:45,145 --> 00:18:45,805
Who can say?

257
00:18:46,405 --> 00:18:47,906
She was rather irresponsible.

258
00:18:48,886 --> 00:18:49,946
Heaven exists.

259
00:18:51,086 --> 00:18:53,006
It's more convenient if it does.

260
00:18:55,427 --> 00:18:55,927
You're right.

261
00:18:57,199 --> 00:18:58,999
I should try believing
for a change.

262
00:19:00,140 --> 00:19:03,000
Do you have any idea exactly
where this place might be?

263
00:19:03,020 --> 00:19:04,781
Let me ponder...

264
00:19:06,281 --> 00:19:08,661
If it's in the north... Enda.

265
00:19:09,982 --> 00:19:11,922
But that's where...
That's correct.

266
00:19:13,322 --> 00:19:15,723
It is now home to the
Demon King's castle.

267
00:19:18,723 --> 00:19:20,344
Why would it be in such a place?

268
00:19:21,504 --> 00:19:26,665
Frieren, you must go to
Aureole and speak with Himmel.

269
00:19:29,643 --> 00:19:31,804
You said you would
help me, did you not?

270
00:19:34,666 --> 00:19:35,986
You've picked up a few tricks.

271
00:19:36,407 --> 00:19:36,687
Where?

272
00:19:37,767 --> 00:19:39,889
I think we both know
the answer to that.

273
00:19:40,649 --> 00:19:41,349
I'll do it then.

274
00:19:42,170 --> 00:19:43,470
We needed a destination.

275
00:19:45,351 --> 00:19:49,334
Though I hate to think I'll be passing through
the tundra around the Demon King's castle.

276
00:19:50,514 --> 00:19:51,695
Maybe I don't want to go.

277
00:19:51,715 --> 00:19:55,337
This is going to
be an uphill battle.

278
00:20:00,993 --> 00:20:02,334
She's already dead asleep.

279
00:20:02,874 --> 00:20:04,215
As carefree as ever.

280
00:20:04,235 --> 00:20:06,537
Too cold.

281
00:20:06,837 --> 00:20:08,739
No one of me is out there.

282
00:20:09,119 --> 00:20:10,260
Sleepwhining.

283
00:20:11,200 --> 00:20:14,022
Is it really that frigid around
the Demon King's castle?

284
00:20:16,924 --> 00:20:19,646
Conquering Indus
terrain is no small feat.

285
00:20:20,287 --> 00:20:22,668
It's at the northernmost
end of the continent.

286
00:20:23,809 --> 00:20:26,971
We braved much more
than the cold in that place.

287
00:20:28,372 --> 00:20:28,893
I'm sure.

288
00:20:37,008 --> 00:20:38,368
Feels a little too quiet.

289
00:20:39,729 --> 00:20:41,309
I think she's napped
for long enough.

290
00:20:43,790 --> 00:20:44,750
Nap time's over.

291
00:20:44,770 --> 00:20:46,230
Rise and shine.

292
00:20:49,831 --> 00:20:50,912
Well, I tried.

293
00:20:51,652 --> 00:20:52,752
Say, Fern.

294
00:20:54,433 --> 00:20:56,153
Is that elf a good
teacher to you?

295
00:20:57,771 --> 00:20:58,951
That's a fair question.

296
00:20:58,971 --> 00:21:00,932
I don't know the answer.

297
00:21:00,952 --> 00:21:05,012
She just drags me around on
her aimless search for new spells.

298
00:21:05,872 --> 00:21:07,293
I'm always at her mercy.

299
00:21:08,293 --> 00:21:14,214
That said, her interest in getting to know Himmel and
the rest of your party has given her some direction.

300
00:21:15,494 --> 00:21:19,355
When it comes to me, I find that
she is significantly less interested.

301
00:21:20,815 --> 00:21:26,576
The reason she took me on in the first place
was because Master Heiter asked her to.

302
00:21:28,844 --> 00:21:29,404
I see.

303
00:21:31,146 --> 00:21:33,947
But, well, she does
care in her own way.

304
00:21:34,748 --> 00:21:39,411
Whenever my birthday comes around,
she picks out some sort of present for me.

305
00:21:40,952 --> 00:21:43,393
She usually seems
indifferent to my presents.

306
00:21:44,834 --> 00:21:46,675
I'm curious what
goes through her mind.

307
00:21:47,596 --> 00:21:48,556
She's a mystery.

308
00:21:54,540 --> 00:21:57,422
Frieren, you won't be
staying in the Royal Capital?

309
00:21:58,585 --> 00:21:59,785
I'm going to keep traveling.

310
00:22:00,485 --> 00:22:01,246
All by yourself?

311
00:22:01,566 --> 00:22:02,586
It's easier that way.

312
00:22:03,806 --> 00:22:05,827
You're not going to
take on an apprentice.

313
00:22:06,647 --> 00:22:08,807
A journey is better
with someone to talk to.

314
00:22:08,827 --> 00:22:11,468
I fear it would be
a waste of time.

315
00:22:12,168 --> 00:22:14,648
No matter how much I
teach them, they'll surely die.

316
00:22:17,209 --> 00:22:18,149
Algeria.

317
00:22:19,450 --> 00:22:21,450
That's not how
relationships work.

318
00:22:22,336 --> 00:22:23,457
That's how they work for me.

319
00:22:24,237 --> 00:22:25,638
Just consider our adventure.

320
00:22:26,259 --> 00:22:28,781
It's taken up less than one
one-hundredth of my life.

321
00:22:30,082 --> 00:22:31,443
You should understand, Eisen.

322
00:22:35,365 --> 00:22:36,046
That's enough!

323
00:22:36,526 --> 00:22:38,308
No time for such
depressing talk!

324
00:22:38,548 --> 00:22:40,889
Today is a day for
celebration and glee!

325
00:22:41,130 --> 00:22:42,010
Let us toast!

326
00:22:42,350 --> 00:22:44,992
It sounds like somebody
wants an excuse to drink more.

327
00:22:45,172 --> 00:22:46,353
Was the veil so thin?

328
00:22:46,914 --> 00:22:48,535
The veil was transparent.

329
00:22:49,123 --> 00:22:50,804
The corrupt priest
strikes again.

330
00:22:50,824 --> 00:22:59,910
Fern, that elf is
a great teacher.

331
00:23:02,712 --> 00:23:03,353
You're right.

332
00:23:08,716 --> 00:23:10,358
You're really not
coming with us?

333
00:23:11,438 --> 00:23:11,979
Correct.

334
00:23:12,779 --> 00:23:16,502
It's as I told you before, I
would only get in your way.

335
00:23:18,519 --> 00:23:18,919
All right.

336
00:23:20,100 --> 00:23:22,742
You remember the
path to Inder, don't you?

337
00:23:23,582 --> 00:23:23,903
Yes.

338
00:23:24,443 --> 00:23:25,844
We'll go through
the Villa Region.

339
00:23:26,484 --> 00:23:30,127
Then we'll cross Regal Canyon and
find the Northern Lands Checkpoint.

340
00:23:32,869 --> 00:23:33,549
Forgive me.

341
00:23:34,570 --> 00:23:36,611
You have a long journey ahead.

342
00:23:37,632 --> 00:23:39,673
It took the four
of us ten years.

343
00:23:42,335 --> 00:23:42,835
I see.

344
00:23:43,576 --> 00:23:48,019
So we'll be following the same route you took to
the Demon King's castle on your first journey.

345
00:24:14,713 --> 00:24:15,433
That we will.

346
00:24:16,754 --> 00:24:18,555
Another brief
ten-year adventure.

